– Jinbe!

30
00:02:11.440 --> 00:02:15.530
Everyone! From this day forward,
I'm a part of the Sunny's crew.

31
00:02:19.410 --> 00:02:21.120
I was so worried about you!

32
00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:23.670
I missed you!

33
00:02:24.080 --> 00:02:26.130
Boss!

34
00:02:27.960 --> 00:02:31.510
I'm happy to see all of you again, too!

35
00:02:33.420 --> 00:02:36.890
To think Jinbe, a former Warlord,
has joined our crew...!

36
00:02:36.890 --> 00:02:38.760
I feel better already!

37
00:02:40.310 --> 00:02:42.140
I'm so glad you're alright!

38
00:02:46.230 --> 00:02:47.650
Nami...

39
00:02:47.650 --> 00:02:49.900
you don't have to hug him that hard...

40
00:02:56.740 --> 00:03:00.160
You really had us worried, jerk!

41
00:03:00.160 --> 00:03:02.540
Sorry, sorry!

42
00:03:02.910 --> 00:03:06.830
I had to tend to the Sun Pirates' wounded,

43
00:03:06.830 --> 00:03:09.340
and my farewell party was quite lively,

44
00:03:09.840 --> 00:03:12.210
so it was hard to leave.

45
00:03:12.210 --> 00:03:14.340
Sorry about that.

46
00:03:15.010 --> 00:03:17.050
Everyone, once again...

47
00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:22.010
I look forward to traveling with you!

48
00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:29.400
Jinbe's steering skills are the real deal!

49
00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:32.020
He surfed a wave with the Sunny!

50
00:03:32.020 --> 00:03:33.650
I see...

51
00:03:34.320 --> 00:03:40.200
Finally, someone showed up who can
tap into my dream ship's potential...

52
00:03:40.530 --> 00:03:42.120
Let's make a toast!

53
00:03:42.120 --> 00:03:43.870
Alright!

54
00:03:45.750 --> 00:03:48.080
Time for a toast!

55
00:03:48.080 --> 00:03:49.080
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

56
00:03:49.080 --> 00:03:50.750
Hey, hold on!

57
00:03:50.750 --> 00:03:53.380
We don't have any booze on board!

58
00:03:53.380 --> 00:03:54.590
Actually...

59
00:03:56.130 --> 00:03:58.010
I smell booze...

60
00:03:58.430 --> 00:03:59.430
From where?!

61
00:03:59.800 --> 00:04:00.800
Over there.

62
00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:01.720
Huh?

63
00:04:05.100 --> 00:04:07.100
Hey!

64
00:04:07.100 --> 00:04:09.020
Sir Luffy!

65
00:04:09.690 --> 00:04:14.900
I wish to discuss what we will do
once we reach Onigashima!

66
00:04:14.900 --> 00:04:19.950
We request your presence at once, Sir Luffy!

67
00:04:20.490 --> 00:04:21.620
You liar!

68
00:04:21.620 --> 00:04:23.660
All I smell is seawater!

69
00:04:23.660 --> 00:04:25.120
I'm not lying!

70
00:04:27.660 --> 00:04:29.750
I smell food, too!

71
00:04:29.750 --> 00:04:32.540
Sir Luffy!

72
00:04:32.540 --> 00:04:33.840
Forget it, Kin.

73
00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:37.220
Making a plan with them is pointless.

74
00:04:39.720 --> 00:04:41.840
Besides, this is my ship.

75
00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:44.430
Take the strategy meeting somewhere else.

76
00:04:54.440 --> 00:04:59.320
This strategy of yours...
I should like to hear it as well!

77
00:04:59.320 --> 00:05:04.280
"Full-Power" Shishilian

Commander of Inuarashi's Musketeers

78
00:05:05.580 --> 00:05:07.540
Full-Power Shishilian!

79
00:05:07.540 --> 00:05:12.460
In this battle, Duke Inuarashi
will fight as Kozuki Oden's retainer!

80
00:05:12.460 --> 00:05:15.880
Therefore, I shall lead the minks!

81
00:05:15.880 --> 00:05:18.130
Right, I leave it to you!

82
00:05:18.130 --> 00:05:19.840
Allow me...

83
00:05:21.340 --> 00:05:26.390
to lead the charge for all of Wano's samurai!

84
00:05:26.390 --> 00:05:30.140
Hyogoro "the Flower"

Former Big Boss of Wano's Underground

85
00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:32.690
Boss Hyogoro!

86
00:05:32.690 --> 00:05:36.690
I must apologize for my absence
over these past twenty years.

87
00:05:36.690 --> 00:05:38.440
I am glad to see you looking well.

88
00:05:38.990 --> 00:05:44.820
Now then, let's get to planning
our arrival at Onigashima already.

89
00:05:44.820 --> 00:05:45.740
Yes.

90
00:05:45.740 --> 00:05:50.870
Didn't I tell them that
this ship isn't a day care?

91
00:05:50.870 --> 00:05:51.830
All right!

92
00:05:52.370 --> 00:05:56.840
I will now present the plan to raid Onigashima!

93
00:05:57.250 --> 00:05:58.750
As shown on this map...

94
00:05:59.300 --> 00:06:04.390
Onigashima

95
00:05:59.420 --> 00:06:03.680
Onigashima is an island surrounded by
mountains on its perimeter.

96
00:06:04.430 --> 00:06:08.430
Any attempt to approach by sea
is thwarted by the sheer cliffs.

97
00:06:09.180 --> 00:06:10.680
It's impossible!

98
00:06:10.680 --> 00:06:16.520
There is but one way to enter the island:
by passing through the front gate!

99
00:06:17.270 --> 00:06:22.490
The skull is part of the mountains,
and there is a castle built within it.

100
00:06:22.490 --> 00:06:25.490
By obtaining the mansion's blueprints,

101
00:06:25.490 --> 00:06:29.740
we learned that the castle
possesses a rear entrance!

102
00:06:27.740 --> 00:06:29.740
Back Door

103
00:06:30.080 --> 00:06:34.500
So we are going to avoid
the heavily guarded front gate,

104
00:06:34.500 --> 00:06:38.340
separate into two groups, take
the mountain paths on the left and right,

105
00:06:34.500 --> 00:06:40.380
Back Door

106
00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:40.380
and sneak in through the back door.

107
00:06:41.550 --> 00:06:46.140
We will launch a surprise attack
on Kaido while he is drunk from the feast,

108
00:06:46.140 --> 00:06:49.140
and end this in one fell swoop!

109
00:06:52.560 --> 00:06:54.390
Brilliant...

110
00:06:54.390 --> 00:07:04.490
Yes, I see this is the same childish plan
you told Kanjuro to deceive him...

111
00:07:04.490 --> 00:07:05.360
Uh...

112
00:07:05.860 --> 00:07:08.320
So, what is your real plan?

113
00:07:09.950 --> 00:07:11.830
What?!

114
00:07:11.830 --> 00:07:14.040
Here we go again, the overestimation.

115
00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:15.000
First...

116
00:07:15.580 --> 00:07:18.170
assuming the enemy is aware of our raid,

117
00:07:18.630 --> 00:07:23.380
their main targets will be
the Red Scabbards samurai!

118
00:07:24.420 --> 00:07:26.760
Plus me,

119
00:07:27.510 --> 00:07:30.550
Straw Hat, and Eustass...

120
00:07:30.550 --> 00:07:32.390
We three captains.

121
00:07:33.390 --> 00:07:34.140
Indeed!

122
00:07:34.140 --> 00:07:37.770
No matter what kind of plan you make,

123
00:07:37.770 --> 00:07:42.320
we know there are two idiots who
will charge in through the front door!

124
00:07:45.320 --> 00:07:50.860
Idiots

125
00:07:45.820 --> 00:07:47.820
Those idiots will make a good diversion...

126
00:07:47.820 --> 00:07:51.450
and they're far stronger than ordinary decoys.

127
00:07:50.860 --> 00:07:50.900
Idiots

128
00:07:50.900 --> 00:07:50.950
Idiots

